I'm Joe Muldowney, veteran of 40 years of running. My best marathon time is 2:22:54,
and, at age 57, I ran the 2010 Philadelphia in a time of 2:58:56. I am the author of the
books: "Running Shorts: A Collection of Stories and Advice for Anyone Who Has Ever
Laced Up a Pair of Running Shoes,." and "Personal Best." I have been the head cross
country coach at Penn State Schuylkill University since 2007, coaching 3 state
champions and an All-American.

Jessica Chan found yoga during some uncertain times in her life and fell in love
with the mind and body connection in the practice. She had been practicing consistently for three years when she decided to take her yoga teacher training on the beautiful island of Koh Samui, Thailand in 2019. This was an unforgettable experience for her
where she got to deepen her yoga practice and learn more about herself. Since completing her Yoga Certification (RYS 200 Yoga Alliance) she has been teaching group classes, one - on - ones and now, online. It has been an amazing start to her teaching
career and she is ecstatic to be sharing this practice.

author.description:
Jamie is a fitness instructor and drummer from St. Andrews in Scotland, with both a
passion for music and a keen interest in fitness! Originally a music student, Jamie graduated from Edinburgh Napier University in 2013 with a First Class degree in BA Popular Music (Hons). After quickly realising that she couldn’t immediately graduate and move on to become a rock star, Jamie started teaching drums to a variety of students and kept up a strong and much - needed yoga practice to keep her body supple and strong for the drum kit.

Jamie is a fitness instructor and drummer from St. Andrews in Scotland, with both a
passion for music and a keen interest in fitness! Originally a music student, Jamie graduated from Edinburgh Napier University in 2013 with a First Class degree in BA Popular Music (Hons). After quickly realising that she couldn’t immediately graduate and move on to become a rock star, Jamie started teaching drums to a variety of students and kept up a strong and much - needed yoga practice to keep her body supple and strong for the drum kit.

exercise.title: Mountain climber
exercise.instructions:
# Start from a high plank position with your hands stacked directly under your shoulders.
# Drive one knee forward toward your chest while engaging your abs.
# Return to your plank position, then drive the knee of your opposite foot in. Repeat the movement, alternating legs and speeding up your movements.
exercise.tips:
# If you’re just learning this move, keep your buttocks higher than your hips. Slow down the movement, keeping weight centered to protect your shoulders.
# Once you’ve mastered the basics, keep your buttocks low and level with your shoulders and move your legs at a faster pace.
# If this exercise strains your wrists, hold onto flat-edged dumbbells instead of putting your hands flat on the floor to alleviate wrist pain.
